    public static enum InstanceInfo.Status
extends Enum<InstanceInfo.Status>
    The status of the instance.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      PROVISIONING
      Indicates that resources are being reserved for the instance.
      RUNNING
      Indicates that the instance is booting up or running.
      STAGING
      Indicates that resources have been acquired and the instance is being prepared for launch.
      STOPPING
      Indicates that the instance is being stopped either due to a failure, or the instance being shut down.
      TERMINATED
      Indicates that the instance was shut down or encountered a failure, either through the API or from inside the guest.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • PROVISIONING

        public static final InstanceInfo.Status PROVISIONING
        Indicates that resources are being reserved for the instance. The instance isn't running yet.

      • STAGING

        public static final InstanceInfo.Status STAGING
        Indicates that resources have been acquired and the instance is being prepared for launch.

      • RUNNING

        public static final InstanceInfo.Status RUNNING
        Indicates that the instance is booting up or running. You should be able to ssh into the instance soon, though not immediately, after it enters this state.

      • STOPPING

        public static final InstanceInfo.Status STOPPING
        Indicates that the instance is being stopped either due to a failure, or the instance being shut down. This is a temporary status and the instance will move to TERMINATED.

      • TERMINATED

        public static final InstanceInfo.Status TERMINATED
        Indicates that the instance was shut down or encountered a failure, either through the API or from inside the guest. You can choose to restart the instance or delete it.
